Built and deployed. **TheFloorIsLava.dll v1.3.1**.

### Why both bugs happened, and the fixes

**Bug 1 — Player not killed**
The deeper dump revealed:

```
=== UT_DamagePlayer (base=MonoBehaviour) ===
  method Void DamagePlayer(Single amount)    ← INSTANCE method, not static
```

I was invoking it with `Invoke(null, …)` which threw a `TargetException`. The `catch` swallowed it silently and your bar/spikes still cleared because `_hp.Dead` was true. The proper kill method, which directly drives the game's death flow, is `ENT_Player.Kill(string)` (inherited from `GameEntity`):

```60:84:c:\Users\TFS\Documents\projects\White Knuckle Mod\SpikeBalanceMod\GameRefs.cs
    public static bool KillPlayer(string reason = "Lava")
    {
        var p = Player();
        if (p == null)
        {
            Plugin.LogInfo("KillPlayer: no player found.");
            return false;
        }
        if (KillString == null)
        {
            Plugin.LogInfo("KillPlayer: ENT_Player.Kill(string) not found.");
            return false;
        }
        try
        {
            KillString.Invoke(p, new object[] { reason });
            return true;
        }
```

Exceptions now log to `LogOutput.log` instead of being swallowed. The death reason is `"Lava"`, which should show in the run-end screen.

**Bug 2 — Black spikes**
