```

Cloning preserves the level shader (URP/Lit, HDRP/Lit, Standard, whatever the game uses) and all its texture bindings — so the cone gets the exact same surface as a nearby wall, just tinted lighter. The dump now prints the shader + texture name so we can verify in the log on the next run. Sampling happens once per `ScanScene` until it succeeds, so as soon as level geometry loads the cones get the texture.

