Deployed. Three things changed to track down the disappearing tablet:

1. **Killed the `CL_Prop` clone path.** The most likely culprit was the cloned game entity deactivating itself inside `CL_Prop.Start()`/`GameEntity.Start()` (entity ID collisions, missing scene references, or `dead`/`destroyObject` getting tripped). The egg now goes straight to a clean self-built physics object that the game's entity system never touches.

2. **Spawn position is now camera-relative**, not player-root-relative. Player root can be at feet OR head depending on the rig, so `playerPos + up*0.3` could easily have been inside the player capsule.

```104:124:c:\Users\TFS\Documents\projects\White Knuckle Mod\SpikeBalanceMod\EasterEgg.cs
        // Spawn at the camera's forward vector, NOT at the player root. Player
        // root can be at the feet (so +0.3y is inside the body and the prop
        // spawns inside the player capsule), or it can be at head-height — we
        // don't know. Camera + forward is reliably "where the player is
        // looking" and is guaranteed to be visible.
        var cam = Camera.main;
        Vector3 camPos, camFwd;
        if (cam != null)
        {
            camPos = cam.transform.position;
            camFwd = cam.transform.forward;
        }
        else
        {
            camPos = player.transform.position + Vector3.up * 1.6f;
            camFwd = player.transform.forward;
        }
```

Spawn lands ~0.7 m in front of the camera and slightly below the sight line, with `Camera.main.transform.forward` flattened so it doesn't shoot down into the floor.

3. **Hardened physics + diagnostics.** The new prop uses `ContinuousDynamic` collision detection (no tunneling through the thin Y axis), interpolation enabled, a much gentler ~0.5 N·s impulse instead of 1.6, and slightly oversized collider (`0.45 × 0.05 × 0.12`). After spawn we log everything needed to diagnose if it's still invisible:

```167:175:c:\Users\TFS\Documents\projects\White Knuckle Mod\SpikeBalanceMod\EasterEgg.cs
        var rends = _droppedProp.GetComponentsInChildren<MeshRenderer>(true);
        var firstMr = rends.Length > 0 ? rends[0] : null;
