            $"EasterEgg: HP-bar tablet spawned as '{_droppedProp.name}' " +
            $"pos={_droppedProp.transform.position} active={_droppedProp.activeInHierarchy} " +
            $"renderers={rends.Length} firstMrEnabled={firstMr?.enabled} " +
            $"firstMatShader='{firstMr?.sharedMaterial?.shader?.name}' " +
            $"bounds={firstMr?.bounds.ToString() ?? "n/a"}. Lava damage is now disabled.");
```

Trigger the egg one more time and share the lines from `EasterEgg: spawning HP-bar prop…` through `…Lava damage is now disabled` in the BepInEx log. That will tell us instantly:

- if `renderers=1` and `firstMrEnabled=True` → object is alive and rendering, just out of your view → I'll fix the spawn pose (closer / higher).
- if `firstMatShader='Hidden/InternalErrorShader'` → the material is the magenta-error fallback → I'll switch shader.
- if `pos=(NaN, NaN, NaN)` or `active=False` → something is killing it post-spawn → I'll guard against that.
- if no `EasterEgg: spawning` line appears at all → the gesture/animation never reached `SpawnDroppedHpBar` → I'll fix the state machine.

Also `EasterEgg: HP-bar material built with shader '<name>'` is now logged the first time the material is constructed — that confirms which shader Unity actually found.

